One-hidden-layer Predictive Coding MNIST model
======================================================================
OneHiddenPC()

Total parameters: 102,544

Shape meaning
-------------
MNIST image x:           [B, 1, 28, 28]
Flattened image x_flat:  [B, 784]
Label one-hot y:         [B, 10]
Hidden state h:          [B, 128]
W_x hidden->image:       [128, 784]
W_y label->hidden:       [10, 128]

PC equations
------------
predicted_input  = h @ W_x + b_x
predicted_hidden = y_one_hot @ W_y + b_h
eps_input        = x_flat - predicted_input
eps_hidden       = h - predicted_hidden
E_PC             = recon_weight * 0.5 * mean(eps_input^2)
                 + hidden_weight * 0.5 * mean(eps_hidden^2)

Training difference from backprop
---------------------------------
Backprop: x -> network -> logits -> CE loss -> loss.backward() -> optimizer.step()
PC here:  clamp x and y -> infer h for many steps -> update W_x and W_y from errors
======================================================================
Using local PC error-based weight updates with lr=0.02

